<html><head></head><body dir=3D"auto" style=3D"overflow-wrap: =
break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; line-break: after-white-space;">Hi =
Chris,<div><br></div><div><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: =
pre-wrap;">Thank you so much for sending the Asset Restore scope of =
works and for all the work you=E2=80=99re putting into moving my claim =
forward. I really appreciate your support and the effort to get things =
rolling.</p><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">As just =
discussed over the phone, I=E2=80=99d love to chat about a few things to =
ensure we=E2=80=99re covering all safety bases and tackling this in the =
best order. While I=E2=80=99m excited to move ahead, I would  feel more =
at ease knowing everything=E2=80=99s been thoroughly checked. I hope you =
don=E2=80=99t mind me asking=E2=80=94your guidance would be a huge =
help!</p><ul dir=3D"auto"><li>Could we prioritize these assessments =
first?<ul dir=3D"auto"><li>A master electrician has flagged the property =
as unsafe, particularly with the switchboard and cabling. Would it be =
possible to arrange a licensed electrical inspection to confirm safety =
before anyone re-enters?</li><li>As we spoke, there are structural beam =
damages, and the significant smoke traveling through floors, walls, and =
out all sides of the roof suggests extensive heat stress. The wetness =
and dampness created by firefighters might have added to the structural =
issues too. Might it be safer to have a structural engineer assess the =
building before any removal or cleaning starts?</li><li>The quote covers =
&lt;10m=C2=B2 ACM removal, but the attached photo shows the fire-damaged =
deck section connects to the larger area, hinting at more involvement. =
Could we schedule a full asbestos inspection to be certain?</li><li>The =
gas unit, located where heat and smoke hit hardest, is a concern. Would =
it be okay to have a gas technician check the fittings for =
safety?</li><li>The fire brigade=E2=80=99s water use and a subsequent =
leak shutdown suggest potential water damage or mould behind walls. =
Could we arrange a moisture/mould inspection before =
reinstatement?</li></ul></li><li>For safety and planning, would it make =
sense to start with cleaning and removal just for assessment purposes? =
This way, we can uncover any hidden damage (e.g., behind linings) and =
plan the full restoration with confidence. What do you =
think?</li></ul><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: =
pre-wrap;"><br></p><p dir=3D"auto"><span style=3D"white-space-collapse: =
preserve;">I=E2=80=99d also love to receive plans, reports, and quotes =
ahead of time if possible. I only learned about this quote today after =
following up, though it seems it=E2=80=99s been ready for a week. I know =
you=E2=80=99re all busy behind the scenes, and a quick heads-up would =
help me stay informed and involved=E2=80=94would that work?
Please know I=E2=80=99m not trying to slow things down! I=E2=80=99m keen =
to get back home soon=E2=80=94the accommodation allowance is tight, and =
I miss my normal routine. I just want to ensure we=E2=80=99re doing this =
safely and thoroughly. I=E2=80=99d be happy to discuss any of this =
whenever suits you.</span><span style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Thanks =
again for your amazing support. Looking forward to your =
thoughts!</span></p><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: =
pre-wrap;">Kind regards,<br>
Raffaella del =
Prete</p><div><br></div><div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div =
class=3D"AppleOriginalContents" style=3D"direction: ltr;"><blockquote =
type=3D"cite"><div>On 26 Jun 2025, at 9:25=E2=80=AFAM, Chris Cornwall =
